column11: Description

Outstanding Residence with Separate Granny Flat It\'s not often we see an architecturally designed masterpiece such as this, come to market. Outstanding in position, design, features and construction.....you won\'t find another home like it.  This unique home is a two story design and will accommodate the largest of families. The entry is light, airy and provides access to the large, double garage that has plenty of extra storage space. Head up stairs and arrive in the spacious and open plan lounge room, boasting picturesque views of Lake Wollumboola, park land and the ocean. Step out onto the South West facing balcony and enjoy the serene surroundings. Main bedroom with walk in robe and ensuite also sits at the front of the home taking in the view. Galley style kitchen with ample cupboard space, dishwasher and pendant lighting. Move through to the sun filled, North facing end of the house with dining room and a separate lounge room that could be used as another bedroom. Step out onto the North East facing balcony to enjoy the sunshine and the sound of the waves. High ceilings throughout upstairs, large windows and timber flooring give the home a bright and airy feel. Down stairs is a 2 bedroom flat, completely separate with its own parking bay. It has a neat and tidy kitchen, open plan dining and living space, tiled throughout and built in robes.  Set on a 870sqm block located directly across from Lake Wollumboolla. With Warrain Beach merely 150 meters away this is an ideal family holiday home, beach side residence or investment property with the potential to use the home and rent out the granny flat.

Absolute Waterfront Living Surround yourself with nature in this serene piece of paradise, a truly unique opportunity to slip straight into the laid-back lifestyle this property offers. Positioned on a beautifully maintained 686 sqm, the immaculate home presents extremely comfortable living with a tranquil outlook over the canal to the trees.  Entertain on the stylish covered alfresco deck by the water\'s edge, throw a line in off your jetty or just sit and watch fish jumping, ducks swimming and kangaroos feeding. Launch your boat from your private slipway and hit the lake for a fish, ski or a leisurely cruise along the extensive waterways of Lake Conjola. And if you want even more, find the shops, caf, bowling club and beach all within a short stroll from the front door. Additional features: Master bedroom with generous built-ins and ensuite Two additional double bedrooms with built-ins Main bathroom with relaxing spa bath, perfect for chilly winter nights Two living areas divided by a brilliant atrium Reverse cycle air-conditioning, ceiling fans, gas heating and solar hot water Tandem garage with roller door access to backyard The vendors are motivated so enquire today, this dream could become your reality.

A wonderful opportunity for first home buyers, those looking to downsize or investors. Occupying a 651m2 block and situated in a quiet cul-de-sac this freestanding home has been partially renovated internally for maximum appeal. Equipped with family lounge, dining and a stylish kitchen complete with centre island bench and 3 ample bedrooms. In an ideal setting, only a short drive to Illaroo Road Public School, Local shops, Medical services and Bushwalks along the banks of the Shoalhaven River - Three ample sized bedrooms - Quality kitchen boasts a dishwasher, and generous storage - 3 way bathroom with shower & bath - Single detached garage - Large timber deck for year round entertaining - Side access to the rear yard and garage - Pet-friendly fully fenced rear yard - Easy to maintain gardens - Vibrant convenience to all local amenities such as North Nowra Medical Centre, North Nowra shops, Illaroo Road Public School and The Grotto walking track To arrange an inspection contact the selling agent at Professionals Real Estate Nowra on 4421 2644

MODERN, EASY CARE LIFESTYLE This as new 4-year-old home was built by a local builder and designed for easy care, comfortable living. With quality fixtures through out and an easy flow floor plan, you will be impressed with all the extra features added. Accommodation: 3 bedrooms, all with built in wardrobes, main with ensuite, 2 separate living areas at the front and back of the home, modern light filled kitchen with pantry & dishwasher, spacious main bathroom, internal laundry with ample amount of storage and a single remote garage with internal access. Features: There have been a lot of added features including beautiful polished timber hardwood floors, ducted air, covered alfresco area & patio blinds, carport, solar hot water & 6 x solar panels on roof, caesarstone stone benchtops in kitchen, electric wall oven & cook top, heated towel rack in main bathroom, light dimers, sensor light, ceiling fans, established garden & garden shed. Location: Perfectly positioned within close proximity to Nowras CBD, everything you need is only minutes away. Located at the back of a battle axe block, it gives you a little more privacy. This home would be great for buyers looking to downsize, first home buyers or an investor wanting something new that you could move a tenant straight into. A FEEL GOOD FAMILY HOME AMONGST LEAFY SERENITY Offering a unique opportunity for the astute investor or owner occupier, this home enjoys a peaceful position moments from all of ULLADULLA\'s conveniences. Opening to capture a leafy outlook over adjoining reserves and bathed in morning light that filters through the treetops, this is a home of wide appeal. Offering an abundance of space, quality and comfort, this family home meets the practical needs of the large modern family. Rear side access is a huge plus allowing you to accommodate your car, trailer, boat or caravan safely out the back and the double garage is remotely controlled for extra convenience.  A strong visible connection to the backyard is made possible through two banks of sliding glass doors that merge the living room and outdoor area. There are 4 generous bedrooms, newly carpeted, painted, all with built in wardrobes and ducted AC units plus the added bonus of a downstairs teenagers or parents retreat. The spacious bathroom features a bath, shower and separate toilet and the walk-through kitchen boasts a dishwasher, stainless steel appliances and plenty of storage.  - Moments from schools, transport, shopping, parkland, restaurants, cafes, beach. Situated on a gently sloping 896sqm block. Solid brick construction, easy-care tile and carpeted floors. A fresh open layout enjoying a bright north easterly aspect. Spacious tiled living spaces with bonus study. Stunning gourmet kitchen with loads of deep drawers and top-line appliances. Bright and private master suite including fully tiled en-suite. With schools, hospitals, shopping and dining precincts, parks and public transport all on your doorstep, it is easy to see why buyers are looking here for the combination of location and convenience. This split level home is made for low maintenance and comfortable living, so you can just move straight in. Impressive private master suite including a dressing area with built-ins and a large ensuite with separate toilet. This brick home is move in ready, with all the modern features you desire.  This is a great opportunity to get into the ULLADULLA market. Inspect, fall in love, make your offer and own! This one won\'t last long. Call Joel on 0402 550 693 to view today. Location & Lifestyle!!! A rare opportunity to acquire such a well established property in one of the quietest locations in VINCENTIA, yet one of the most convenient. The home has been in the same family for many years and has been well cared for and now is it\'s time for a new owner and whether you are looking at a Sea Change, a New Family home, an investment or Holiday home you will not be disappointed. A very solid brick home situated on a fully fenced 695m2 block Flowing lounge and dining areas flooded with natural light  Parquetry flooring throughout the upstairs living area  Large upstairs entertainers deck over looking the reserve  A well appointed kitchen with a walk-in pantry  4 good sized bedrooms with built-in wardrobes Main bedroom with ensuite and huge built-in wardrobe  Ample storage, including cellar area and air conditioning Double garage with internal access  And all located in a peaceful cul-de-sac opposite a reserve and within a very easy walk to Blue waters and sandy beaches of Jervis Bay and a short drive to the shopping centres of Vincentia and the Cafes, Pub and Restaurants of Huskisson. The location alone is worthy of an inspection and will not last so do not delay in organising a time to see this fantastic property.

Come home to paradise This light-filled, airy and comfortable home has been beautifully maintained and updated, there is nothing more to do other than move on in. Surrounded by flowering trees and native plants, the birdlife adds to the serenity. The wrap around verandah offers privacy and an elevated leafy view from all angles. The kitchen has been recently updated and features stainless steel appliances including gas cooktop, electric oven, range hood and dishwasher that flows onto a large open plan living area with R/C air conditioner, remote controlled ceiling fans and gas outlet points. This area also opens onto a large covered outdoor alfresco area with ceiling fan and gas outlet point, perfect for your BBQ entertaining. There are three comfortable bedrooms, two with built-ins and the main opens onto the east facing deck for that perfect morning cuppa.  The main bathroom has separate shower and bath and a second toilet is conveniently located in the laundry. A large double garage, with work bench, plus carport sits at the rear of the property, accessed by a good concrete driveway and turning area. There is additional room here for a boat or trailer. The home has had a lot of recent upgrading including re-painting, ceiling fans and LED lighting throughout, new carpet in the bedrooms, an alarm system, quality gutter guards and a 6.6kw Solar Power back-to-grid generation system making the home very energy efficient. Approximately 200m walk to the boat ramp and pontoon, you can enjoy the waterways of Lake Conjola easily for fishing, boating or kayaking.  Milton and Ulladulla are only a short drive away, yet Fishermans Paradise remains one of the Shoalhaven\'s secret hideaway gems. It\'s close to numerous beaches, lakes and National Parks. The perfect place to raise a family, retire to or use as a getaway from the hustle and bustle. Definitely worth your inspection and consideration. Call Jemma today on 0499 555 843.

An Acre of Space Presented by Able Walsh (0402 299 309) and Kevin Johnston (0423 381 461) of Integrity Real Estate Jervis Bay and St Georges Basin. This property is what dreams are made of, a complete blank canvas with endless opportunities just 200m to Currambene Creek, 5 minutes to Huskisson and all with your own acre of space. At 4000m2 of level, mostly cleared and usable land there is space to make what you want of this one, a big shed, a pool, a bike track, some animals or all of the above if you choose.  The house is original yet immaculate in condition with ample space all around. All of the bedrooms have built in wardrobes, the internal bathroom is a 3 way bathroom whilst there is a second bathroom in the garage (something that could easily be updated into a big 4th bedroom with parents retreat). The main living area is huge with glass sliding doors both front and back meaning the space is light, open and airy. The kitchen is big and has a dining area adjoining and partially open to the main living area also. There is a front patio and back porch and its all waiting for you. There is an oversize garage come workshop, the property is fully fenced, town water is connected and its all waiting for you. - 4000m2 of level & usable land Just 200m to Currambene Creek Just 5 minutes to Huskisson A complete blank canvas A house with lots of space Oversize garage/workshop All waiting for you

UNIQUE BEACHSIDE HOME Surprisingly good ocean and coastline views and a sunny northerly aspect combine to create a cosy and comfortable beachside home. The spacious upper living area with Cypress timber flooring offers views to the leafy reserve, over the mature garden with ornamental trees and to cap off the panorama, northern and eastern views back to the coast. 3 Bedrooms and renovated modern bathroom are all on the upper level with a great outlook and are perfectly located for capturing the north-east summer breeze. The lower tiled living area is cool in Summer and includes a modern new kitchen with Caesarstone bench tops and huge walk-in pantry plus a bathroom/ laundry, walk-in linen closet and single garage with drive through access to the back yard. Fabulous garden spaces can be used for entertaining and there is even a loo out the back. Only 500 metres via stairs to Mollymook Beach and close to restaurants, shops, Bowling & Golf Clubs. Loads of character, this charming home has a relaxed ambience and a great location. * Solar power - 7 Panels * Reverse cycle air conditioning * Backing onto reserve * Walking distance to Mollymook Beach

A Family sized home in sparkling, like new condition. Possibly the best location in town. With quiet tree lined streets, a beautiful mountain backdrop and safe for young and older alike.  4 bedrooms all with built in wardrobes  Master bedroom with ensuite  2 distinct living areas  Large outdoor covered entertaining area Many extras and additions including, 3 reverse cycle air conditioners, ceiling fans, security screens and a double garage with automatic doors. The vehicle accessible rear yard is spacious and secure. With new paintwork and carpets throughout, it looks, feels, and smells like new! This is a quality residence to call home. To arrange your inspection, contact the selling agent Professional Real Estate Nowra. You will not be disappointed.

NEAR NEW 3 BEDROOMS IN MILTON This near-new three-bedroom, single level home is ideal for downsizers, with a large single garage plus two parking spaces, perfect for the van or boat. A contemporary kitchen features gas cooktop, electric oven and a glass splashback, flowing onto an open plan living area with timber-look flooring. A north-facing hardwood timber deck has a leafy outlook and privacy screening, making it ideal for entertaining family and friends. The master bedroom boasts a walk-in robe and ensuite, while the family bathroom has a shower plus large free-standing bathtub and gleaming marble-look tiles. The home is only two years old with a fresh, modern grey and white colour pallet. The elevated living areas are at the rear and the home is set back off the street, with a stacked stone wall providing privacy. With a fully fenced backyard, the property is low maintenance, so keen travellers can lock up and take off. Located on the fringe of Milton, it\'s away from the busy shopping centre, but still close enough to walk to town with supermarket, cafes, health facilities and library. This property would also be ideal for first home-buyers or investors looking for an affordable home in trendy Milton.

Panoramic Ocean  Views Enjoying a commanding hilltop position in one of Mollymooks most sought after streets, this original home boasts sweeping ocean panoramas and a perfect north easterly aspect. Features a flexible single level layout with 2 bedrooms, large family/rumpus room, electric kitchen, lock-up garage with internal access. Blissfully quiet, sun drenched and surrounded by quality homes, the elevated aspect of this home ensures never-to-be-built-out views. There is endless potential to create a coastal masterpiece moments from beach, cafes and golf club. Features include: 2 bedrooms family/rumpus room electric kitchen lounge & dining areas with views front balcony with views easy-care tiled floors fenced yard single garage with internal access moments to beach & cafes endless potential 645sqm
easy to own promising lifestyle excellence  quiet street with leafy outlook renovated kitchen; ducted air-con easy care yard with huge pergola convenient to North Nowra shops

Exclusively Positioned Family Home Sam Werry from CENTURY 21 Signature Realty in Nowra is proud to present 22 Amalfi Crescent in Nowra.  Showcasing undisturbed views over Lyrebird Park to Cambewarra Mountain and beyond, this two-story family home is set on a 614 sqm block. Recently renovated enhancing an already sound home in a quiet and convenient location you will be impressed with the generous floorplan accommodating any number of family dynamics. The home features 5 generous bedrooms, 2 renovated bathrooms, separate lounge and dining areas, a functional sunlit kitchen with dishwasher and wall oven. The double lock-up garage with additional driveway space for extra vehicles completes this desirable residence. Features: Unobstructed views of Lyrebird Park and Cambewarra Mountain 2 car garage plus extra driveway space 614 sqm block Spacious living area 5 Bedrooms, all with built-ins 2 bathrooms w/ separate toilets Rear covered entertaining area Fully fenced rear yard In a premier position within easy walking distance to the CBD, local schools and shopping centres, this fantastic family home offers plenty of bang for its buck. Call Sam Werry on 0422 108 228 for further information or to book your digital or physical inspection!

Location  Tick - Large block - Tick This large, elevated and level block is a just a short stroll to Shoalhaven River, shops and club. The charming 1950\'s cottage has high ceilings with some original ornate features such as cornices and beautiful solid timber doors. Living areas are open plan and there is the major bonus of a detached studio or teenagers retreat at rear.  The kitchen has been modernised over the years with gas cooking and dishwasher. The main bathroom is oversized and currently caters for wheelchair access. There is also a second guest toilet. It\'s a perfect rectangular shaped block with a 20-metre frontage and wide side access to the rear of the property. Features   Air-conditioning   Bore water well and pump for gardens  Detached Studio or teenagers retreat at rear  Garden shed and fenced vegetable garden  Gas cooking  Separate study  Large bathroom with 2nd guest toilet

YOUR OWN FAMILY SANCTUARY Abundant, light-filled living spaces; sunny open plan kitchen and an entertaining terrace create the ultimate family entertainer. This perfect home has been solidly built like a fortress, with no expense being spared on the fittings and fixtures throughout. Providing a spacious and private family environment with excellent size, quality and a striking modern design, this smartly appointed home offers a superb lifestyle property. Rear side access is a huge plus allowing you to accommodate your car, trailer, boat or caravan safely out the back and the double garage is remotely controlled for extra convenience.  This property enjoys a peaceful and leafy outlook. There is literally nothing you need to do other than unpack and enjoy what coastal living has to offer. A sliding glass door opens out to an expansive, undercover outdoor entertainment area creating the perfect open space for entertaining guests throughout the year. There\'s enough grassed space for the kids to play and the whole area is fenced. - Near level 556m2 block. Soaring ceilings, polished timber floorboards. Eye-catching structural presence from street level. Selection of living areas for formal or casual gatherings. The functional chef\'s kitchen features an electric stove, double sink, walk in pantry. The main bedroom features a spacious walk-in-wardrobe, plus a stylish ensuite. Effortlessly chic and tastefully decorated, the house offers light filled spacious bedrooms. Luxurious fully tiled bathroom with stylish shower. Great shed and covered workshop, with power for the handyman/hobbyist. The separate family room and meals area takes in the leafy backdrop adjacent to the very well-appointed and stylish kitchen. Upstairs the bedrooms are superbly set out to ensure sought after separation between parents and teenagers. Ideally located in Manyana this impeccable home offers a level of finish that is arguably amongst the best in the street. This type of property doesn\'t come along very often and you do not want to miss this opportunity call Joel on 0402 550 693 now for more information. MASTERBUILT MILTON HOME WITH VIEWS This grand home takes in commanding vistas over Milton farmland and beyond to the coastline and Green Island. With four bedrooms, a dedicated office, plus sprawling living areas over two levels, this property offers a relaxed lifestyle, with upper and lower entertaining decks making the most of the views and the north-east aspect. Upstairs, there is a gourmet kitchen with 40mm Caesarstone benchtops, island bench, gas cooktop and handy servery window opening onto the deck. The light-filled living areas stretch across the rear of the home, with high vaulted ceilings, vinyl flooring, and numerous sliding glass doors opening on to the deck, soaking up the sensational views. The luxurious master bedroom with walk-in robe and ensuite, opens onto a private balcony with postcard views to Green island. The guest bedroom also has an ensuite and built-in robe. Another two well-proportioned bedrooms downstairs open onto a rumpus room with gleaming polished concrete floors, kitchenette and doors opening onto a huge covered and elevated deck. The home is cleverly designed, with a fully fitted office, extra large laundry with laundry shute and loads of storage inside and under the house. Additional features include a double garage, reverse cycle air conditioning, gas fireplace, dual blinds, LED lighting throughout, solar power and hot water, rainwater tanks and the home is fully insulated. This contemporary country style home is close to Milton township with its cafes, trendy boutiques and theatre, and it\'s just a five-minute drive to Mollymook Beach and Ulladulla shopping centre.

Something Special Spacious and modern comes straight to mind when inspecting this beautiful home. Situated on a large 883sm block with backyard access, homes of this calibre don\'t come up this often. On offer here are very generous spaces, high ceilings, a modern colour palette and options that will present to all in the buyers\' market.  2 choices of living spaces and separate dining   Huge master suite with robe and ensuite  A kitchen to die for.sooo much space and storage  Gorgeous bathroom with claw bath  Hobby room/retreat space  Air conditioning, fans and woodfire  Covered outdoor entertaining area with low maintenance gardens  Access to a fantastic shed with extra bathroom and loads of off street room for the caravan, boat or trailer There is too much to list and so much that you are going to love. Located in the top of a secluded cul-de-sac and just 650ms to local shopping centre, Medical Centre and 1 km to popular Illaroo Road Public School.

SINGLE LEVEL HOME - MOVE IN READY Positioned approx 500mtrs from the Paradise Beach, approx 800mtrs to the local shops and a short 2 minute drive to the boat ramp and Country Club with Golf Course. This single level, conveniently located home will suit all buyer types, especially retirees and first home buyers. *Single level four bedroom home, 639m2 flat block. *Generous north facing living/dining and kitchen. *Handy sunroom acts as a 2nd living or T.V. room. *All beds are spacious, beds 1 and 2 with built-ins. *Covered wraparound veranda, great to entertain. *Well-kept home with low maintenance gardens. *Freestanding garage, side access, room for a boat. *3m x 3m garden shed, tucked away in the corner. Whether you are looking for a weekender, rental property or just a place to call home, this property is move-in ready, so don\'t hesitate and book an inspection today. All enquiries or to book a private inspection please contact Scott Morton on either 0405 227 987 or 0244 417 514.

Brand new home plus granny flat. Located on a great corner block, this brand new home has just been completed by a renowned Boutique Builder. Finished to a high standard of quality and packed with features including a self contained granny flat ideal for the extended family or superb investment opportunity. - 4 bedrooms, master with ensuite and large walk-in robe. Quality kitchen with stone benchtop and walk-in pantry 5 burner gas cooktop, 900mm oven and dishwasher. Fully ducted air conditioning system. Beautiful tiled open plan living area and media room. Alfresco outdoor entertaining area with extensive landscaping Spacious granny flat with car accommodation. A very spacious home with all the modern comforts and not a cent to spend offering either home with income or a combined estimated rental return of $770 per week. Just move in and enjoy.

Ticks all the boxes You will be pressed to find a better family home than this ticking all the boxes. Located on the northern side of Bomaderry with easy access to the newly constructed highway making a quick trip to Wollogong and Sydney easy. With a sprawling floor plan there is plenty of space to hangout together, then slip away to the privacy of your own wing. Outside the fun continues with inground pool and spa and an entertainment area suitable for the biggest parties. This is all topped of by every mans dream shed with extra space for caravans, boats and all the toys you can imagine. Inspections are available only by private appointment.

column4: 23 Sir Henry Crescent Callala Beach NSW 2540
column11: Brand New Beauty on Sir Henry Want a 2 or 3 bedroom brand new beach house? Well the choice is yours with this flexible design. Just completed is this brand new designer duplex in a much sort after location in Callala Beach. You will hear the bay as lay in bed only a few hundred meters to Callala Beach on Jervis Bay. Take advantage of the new build grants and get ready to enjoy all that Callala beach has to offer.These are the only brand new homes available in this area and will never be repeated at this price. Be quick to book your private inspection today.

column4: 91 Penguins Head Road Culburra Beach NSW 2540
column11: Master Built Award Winning home, first time offered. The unique design in this immaculately presented home was achieved when the original single storey home was renovated in 2011 to provide an amazing top floor.  Downstairs features original hardwood floors, smart kitchen looking onto back garden, two bedrooms, rustic bathroom and spacious living/dining area opening onto a shuttered deck, perfect for taking in the ocean views while enjoying the abundant sunshine.  Take either the timber stairs or the Acorn stair lift to the luxuriously spacious open plan upper floor with tiled floors and raked timber ceiling. Open the bi-fold doors onto the Juliette balcony to enjoy the ocean vistas. In the cooler months, close the doors, turn on the underfloor heating and enjoy the Heat & Glo gas fireplace while still taking in those views.  The state of the art kitchen with stone benchtops contains Miele appliances, a Billi Eco water system providing instant chilled and boiling water and abundant deep drawers for storage. This is truly a cook\'s delight and looks out onto the ocean with a cafe bench opening onto a separate balcony for those leisurely weekend lunches.  The master suite also enjoys ocean views through the timber louvres which then leads past the walk in robe to the stunning bathroom which has to be seen to be believed. Lay back in the deep freestanding bath or enjoy the double shower looking out onto the landscaped back garden and of course there is underfloor heating to provide ultimate winter comfort.  And then there is the landscaped back garden which provides yet another entertaining area, this time al fresco. A pizza oven adjacent to the pergola and outdoor kitchen off the garage make this property a foodie\'s delight especially with the raised garden beds providing fresh herbs & veggies.  The huge double garage contains the laundry and extra high ceilings allowing plenty of roof top storage and is long enough to take a boat.  Perfectly set on a level 650sqm approx block of land with fully fenced rear yard.  With one of the South Coast\'s most beautiful beaches directly across the road, patrolled in the summer holidays, this is an outstanding location. Tilbury Cove and playground are a short walk away and the local corner store just meters away for great coffee or a burger.  This magnificent property offers a rare opportunity, with potential holiday rental income, or even create a bed and breakfast, or just make this your dream seaside home.

Classic Beachcomber with Ocean Views Tucked away from wind, noise and crowds, this 1970\'s "Beachcomber" style residence has been tastefully renovated. Only steps from the beach and with filtered views of the ocean you will fall in love with this prime location in Culburra Beach.  Featuring 2 large bedrooms and modern bathroom, bright open plan living areas and a downstairs laundry/2nd bathroom with storage, this property really has everything. Recently receiving a face-lift, with modern kitchen featuring large island bench with beautiful timber top, polished hardwood timber floors and large North East facing windows let the sights and sounds of the ocean come into the home, as well plenty of sunlight and sea breeze.  The upper deck is perfect for a morning coffee or afternoon drink. Down stairs laundry and shower is great for when you get back from a surf to chuck the wet-suits and boards away and rinse off. Plenty of off street parking, garden shed and heaps of storage. All on a 475sqm block and less than 1 minute stroll and you are on the sand.  Whether you are looking for a weekend escape, a new seaside home or an investment you can\'t go past this special beach house.

Beautiful Home in a Stunning Location Grand in design and construction, this 4-bedroom home is presented to the market for the first time. From the moment you arrive, walk up the front deck & admire the bespoke garden, step through the front door to soon realise there is more than meets the eye with this property. Open spaces, light & all the modern accessories included within this home, it is definitely a must to inspect. Once you enter, you are showcased with the choice of, 1 out of the 2 master bedrooms that have WIR & ensuite bathrooms in both. The upstairs master has a deep bath tub for a touch of luxury. As you continue through this home you will find a powder room located next to the amazing timber staircase, as the open plan design begins to draw your eyes through to the living spaces and beyond. With an ambiance of natural light flooding in & reflecting off the Caesar stone bench tops the modern kitchen is kitted out with quality appliances and gas cooking. You will notice the glittering from the outside solar salt-chlorinated in-ground pool. Tucked away in the fully fenced yard you will find a fire pit area, undercover back patio & a stylish secret courtyard with modern decorative screens....Take your pick of multiple entertaining spaces. The use of Australian natural hard wood throughout gives a touch of class and luxury.  Some of the other amazing features this house has to offer are, walk in butler\'s pantry & ample storage, double garage with internal access, 2 large bedrooms upstairs with WIR. Second rumpus room upstairs which leads out to a front balcony, perfect to enjoy the afternoon sun. The main bathroom is large with bathtub and modern tiles. Ducted air conditioning for year round comfort and ceiling fans.  This 873m block is found directly opposite Lake Wollumboola & only a short 350m walk to Warrain Beach. With walking tracks and park close by, you are surrounded by nature including rare and native birds and other wild life. Start living the dream coastal lifestyle today.

Walk to Beach Lifestyle Positioned in one of Mollymooks most sought after streets, this freestanding single level, 4 bedroom home embraces easy care living.  Low maintenance gardens and fenced yard are perfect for outdoor entertaining.  A great option for lifestyle buyers with a new modern kitchen featuring quality appliances and WIR plus ensuite to main bedroom. This immaculate home blends perfectly with the neighbouring reserve, privately tucked away in a tranquil location.  There is a newly modernised internal laundry, outdoor shower, oversized garage plus secure storage and workshop.  It is a short stroll to the beach or championship golf course, offering an excellent investment opportunity with capital growth potential. Features include: 4 bedrooms WIR and ensuite to main private tranquil rear yard large single garage large secure storage or workshop internal laundry new modern kitchen with quality appliances flexible floor plan neighbours street bush reserve outdoor shower fenced yard walk to cafes, local clubs and golf courses walk to beach 702sqm block

column4: 14 Caulfield Parade Old Erowal Bay NSW 2540
column11: A Dream Home. A Dream Realised Arguably the best property in Old Erowal Bay, this unique one-of-a-kind home is situated on absolute waterfront reserve. Bespoke and providing water views to the horizon, this residence is substantial and sure to delight in all ways. This home is special. It affords a concept of design, refinement and fit-out rarely offered or seen. Fully redeveloped and situated in an elevated position, a perfect cottage facade flows through to a uniquely fashioned living space that emphasises this home\'s amazing natural lighting, aspect and amenity. Contemporary architectural themes reinforce commercial/industrial design elements that flow seamlessly through multi-level living spaces to an external deck and patio showcasing views that never end. Situated on a 740m2 (approx) fully landscaped block and offering 4 generous bedrooms features include Blackbut hardwood floors throughout, custom kitchen, custom bathrooms, fully landscaped grounds and a multitude of storage options. Additional features include Blackout curtains Eurostyle laundry cabinet fitted out with washer/dryer. Vileroy & Bosch wall mounted toilets. Vola Satin finish bathroom mixers. Custom aluminium window casements and framing. Custom aluminium solid core doors. Tri-split system A/C units. Mere minutes\' drive to all amenities including shopping, services, public transport, the beautiful white sand beaches of Jervis Bay and Booderee national park. This is a once in a lifetime opportunity and a must to inspect.

Art, culture and the beach scene collide in this property to make this designer home somewhat of a talking point, it\'s different and such an interesting property that you will leave dreaming of summer days lapping up the Narrawallee vibe in the myriad of cool spaces around this retreat.  Upstairs the living areas flow to two large entertaining decks with lake vistas. The centrally located kitchen is easily accessible from all entertaining spaces with solid Spotted Gum timber bench tops, hidden pantry, plumbed fridge, integrated dishwasher and Italian cooktop. Also upstairs are 2 bedrooms, the master also opening onto the front deck via large sliding glass doors that take in the view. The luxurious main bathroom is cunningly separated into a guest powder room and private bathing space by full height steel and glass doors with a deep freestanding soaking tub, second vanity and rain shower.  Downstairs the self-contained 3/4 bedroom guest accommodation is perfect for holiday letting or the extended family with floating floors, open plan living and a cool reading/ movie nook (optional bedroom). Large sliding glass doors open onto the lower deck and two stunning garden courtyard areas which include mature natives creating privacy, unique dome lighting, flagstone paving and a large BBQ area.  In the rear garden, tucked away, is a studio cabin which could also be used for overflow accommodation, it is the perfect den with Brushbox lined timber ceilings, kitchenette and French doors, it\'s loaded with character and could be used as an advert for Airbnb with its modish, hipster appeal. Not only is this your chance to buy a designer holiday investment that would let extremely well, you have the stunning turquoise waters of Narrawallee Inlet wilderness areas plus two beaches all within easy reach. Inspections are strictly by appointment. Call now and immerse yourself into the Narrawallee lifestyle. More images will be supplied next week.

The charming 3 bedroom home sits at the front of the block which offers gorgeous views over the pristine waters of Sussex Inlet and you have direct water access to St Georges Basin, plus your boat is moored at your doorstep. No more queuing at the public boat ramps !!! Meticulously maintained, this light filled home boasts a huge galley style kitchen with a fabulous walk in pantry, two living areas, seperate dining area, three bedrooms, central bathroom, separate WC and large internal laundry. And there is plenty of space to extend, if your needs are for a bigger home. The lovely rear alfresco entertaining area even has stunning views up the inlet. And the five garages are just the icing on the cake, as you will need all that space to store the toys that you will need as you embrace the wonderful lifestyle on offer at 188 RIVER ROAD. The majority of the adjoining blocks have been either sub-divided or the owners have taken advantage of the SP3 zoning to create their vision, so I would suggest that there is plenty of potential and space to create some opportunities. (STCA) - Private Jetty with direct access to some of the best fishing waters in the area - Ducted air conditioning  - Short 400m stroll to Sussex town centre with cafes, boutiques, bars and restaurants - Town water as well as bore water for gardens & lawns  - Central concrete driveway provides vehicular access to home - Ample off-street parking for cars, caravans, mobile homes, boats and with easy access to water & walking track There are very few opportunities to acquire a property in this location, which offers such a multitude of options. Ceiling fans and gas heating for comfort all year round.   Move through to the open plan living and dining room that has large sliding glass doors that frame the view of the picturesque backyard. You can enjoy the peaceful sound of the native birds that are attracted by all the beautiful trees and hedges that create a private haven. Modern kitchen with gas cooking, range hood, dishwasher and loads of bench and storage space. Main bathroom with bath tub for the little ones or spoil yourself with bubbles and time out. Internal laundry and plenty of storage. Entertaining will be a breeze with the large, undercover North facing deck. Kick back and relax in the sun and enjoy the privacy of your fully fenced back yard. Perfectly positioned on a level 670sqm approx. block of land with stunning Culburra Beach less than 1km walk away and the banks of the Crookhaven River only 400 meters away, this is an amazing opportunity to secure a seaside residence in a quiet and picturesque street, complete with a picket fence! Perfectly designed for a holiday letting so you can reap the rewards of your investment.
